%% ============================================================
%% WORKED EXAMPLE
%% ============================================================
\section*{How Distance Is Calculated: A Worked Example}

We use the \textbf{rank~2} candidate below to illustrate the calculation step by step.
(The rank~1 match has distance~0 and is trivial; rank~2 shows the full arithmetic.)

\vspace{6pt}

\textbf{Step 1 --- Put every feature on the same scale (standardization).}

Raw values are measured in different units (counts, years, percentages).
Before computing distance we convert each to a \emph{standardized score}: how many
standard deviations above or below the combined average that value sits.

\[
  z = \frac{\text{raw value} - \text{combined average}}{\text{combined spread}}
\]

\vspace{4pt}

{\small
\begin{tabular}{l r r r r}
  \toprule
  \textbf{Feature} &
  \textbf{Target (raw)} &
  \textbf{Candidate (raw)} &
  \textbf{Combined Avg.} &
  \textbf{Combined Spread} \\
  \midrule
<% for row in example_rows %>
  << row.display >> & << row.target_raw >> & << row.cand_raw >> & << row.mean >> & << row.std >> \\
<% endfor %>
  \bottomrule
\end{tabular}
}

\vspace{6pt}

Applying the formula above to each feature gives these standardized scores:

\vspace{4pt}

{\small
\begin{tabular}{l r r}
  \toprule
  \textbf{Feature} &
  \textbf{Target (std.)} &
  \textbf{Candidate (std.)} \\
  \midrule
<% for row in example_rows %>
  << row.display >> & << row.z_target >> & << row.z_cand >> \\
<% endfor %>
  \bottomrule
\end{tabular}
}

\vspace{8pt}

\textbf{Step 2 --- Compute the squared difference for each feature, then sum and take the square root.}

\[
  d \;=\; \sqrt{\,\sum_{i}\,\bigl(z_{\text{target},i} - z_{\text{cand},i}\bigr)^2\,}
\]

\vspace{4pt}

{\small
\begin{tabular}{l r r r}
  \toprule
  \textbf{Feature} & \textbf{Target (std.)} & \textbf{Cand. (std.)} & \textbf{Squared difference} \\
  \midrule
<% for row in example_rows %>
  << row.display >> & << row.z_target >> & << row.z_cand >> & << row.sq_diff >> \\
<% endfor %>
  \midrule
  \textit{Sum} & & & \textit{<< example_sq_sum >>} \\
  \bottomrule
\end{tabular}
}

\vspace{6pt}

\[
  d \;=\; \sqrt{<< example_sq_sum >>} \;=\; \mathbf{<< example_distance >>}
\]

